    <body>
        <p>There are a couple of ways to change the order of slides in a slideshow.</p>
        <p>First, you can open the Edit Slideshow dialog. Select the <span class="Emphasis">Slides</span> tab and use the up and down arrows to adjust the order of the slides.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../Images/slideshow10.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="FlareGuides.FlareWhatsNewGuide,ContributorGuides.ContributorWhatsNewGuide" />
        <p>You can also click and drag the slide structure bars up or down, just as you would move any other structure bars. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Structure_Bars/Moving_Paragraphs_and_Content_with_Structure_Bars.htm">Moving Paragraphs and Other Content with Structure Bars</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../Images/slideshow11.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
